<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910703-0142</DOCNO><DOCID>910703-0142.</DOCID><HL>   South Korea Trade Gap Widens</HL><DATE>07/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><IN>INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC AND MONETARY INDICATORS (IEI)INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND STATISTICS (IEN)INTERNATIONAL TRADE NEWS (TRD)</IN><NS>INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND ANALYSIS (IEN)TRADE ISSUES (TRD)</NS><RE>FAR EAST (FE)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)SOUTH KOREA (SK)</RE><LP>   SEOUL, South Korea -- Burdened by heavy imports, SouthKorea ran a record semiannual trade deficit of $6.34 billionbetween January and June, more than twice as wide as a yearearlier, the Trade and Industry Ministry reported.   In the first six months, South Korean merchandise exportswere tallied at $34.15 billion, up 15% from a year earlier,while imports jumped 24% to $40.49 billion.</LP><TEXT>   In June, however, South Korea posted its smallestone-month trade loss since January, at $56 million, theministry said.   Exports amounted to $6.55 billion in June, up 15% from ayear earlier, and imports were $6.6 billion, up 21%.</TEXT></DOC>